The paper proposes a novel filter for sparse big data that utilizes auxiliary information, which suggests that it could fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of auxiliary information also implies that it could be related to databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of autoencoders, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SI).
